    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>World Briefing | Americas: Mexico: Mediation In Colombian Conflict</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Antonio Betancourt (NYT)</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Betancourt, Antonio</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mexican President Vicente Fox, attending Organization of American States meeting in Ecuador, announces Mexico's willingness to act as mediator between Colombian government and guerrillas in hopes of ending four-decade-long conflict (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The government of President Vicente Fox has offered to serve as a mediator in the four-decade fight between Colombia's government and guerrillas. The offer was announced after the Mexican and Colombian foreign ministers conferred at an Organization of American States meeting in Ecuador. Both governments will seek ways that Mexico can serve as a go-between in negotiations toward a cease-fire.</p>
        <p>Antonio Betancourt (NYT)</p>
      </block>
